Introduction: In the Case Bank of Forest Public Security, is listed as "major case" every year there are dozens of cases. Wildlife engaged in illegal hunting, transport, trading criminals, most of the formation of the underground trade in black chain.

Author | first finance and Economics

In the wake of the COVID-19 outbreak in Wuhan, China's State of wildlife predation has drawn increasing attention from all walks of life.

Let's take a look at some Psycho numbers:

In July 2018, forest police in Jiangxi Province cracked the largest ever wildlife trafficking case, involving more than 17,000 animals! Including MUNTJAC, Water Deer and other provincial and national animal protection, sales network covering 15 provinces.

In November 2018, the Forest Public Security Bureau of Hunan Province reported that 216 pangolins were seized and 129 people were arrested after a huge case of illegal acquisition, transportation and sale of rare and endangered wild animals and their products was solved, this is the largest case of Pangolin solved in Hunan so far.

In December 2018, public security officers of the forest case investigation sub-bureau of the Jilin Provincial Forest Public Security Bureau seized 4,857 dead wild animals, including owls and Hazel grouse, which are the second-class protected animals of the state, in a shop in Huinan County, Tonghua, the state three-level protection of animals such as tits, Roe deer, pine ducks, rabbits, etc. .

……

These are just the tip of the iceberg in China's wildlife consumption market. In forest public security's case storehouse, is classified as "the big case important case" each year has dozens. Wildlife engaged in illegal hunting, transport, trading, most of the formation of the underground trade black chain, a large number of "game" was finally placed on the table.

"So far, there is no accurate and authoritative data to show that China is the largest consumer of wildlife, " said the former head of the State Forestry Administration of the People's Republic of China, is Not to be avoided.

The Wildlife Trade is rife

In the case of wildlife trafficking, announced by the forest police of Jiangxi Province, the consignors bought the goods from a Xinyu man in Jiangxi Province without a license and shipped them to Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province, where they were processed into preserved meat and sold at double the profit.

Investigation by the Special Task Force, this is a nationwide 15 provinces and cities, Jiangxi 11 cities and more than 30 counties illegal hunting, acquisition, transport, sale of wildlife network. The suspects are numerous and have complicated identities, including farmers, workers, business owners, students, and even a number of logistics managers of the Railway Freight Department, who allow criminals to wear railway overalls to enter and leave the freight yards freely, a large number of wild animals were illegally distributed across the country through logistics channels.

In addition, there are local wildlife protection and management department staff for illegal elements to issue transport documents, acting as an umbrella to facilitate criminal activities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
17,000! Jiangxi holds largest wildlife trafficking case in history. Source: Forest Public Security

In Chengbu Miao Autonomous County, in the province of Shaoyang, there is also a whole industrial chain of illegal hunting, buying, selling and processing of wild animals. According to the local forest public security bureau, illegal criminal gangs hunt and kill and trade wild animals such as snakes, badgers and masked palm civets, and have verified that the funds involved in the case amount to more than 3 million yuan, the suspects, including hunters, traders, transportation practitioners, distributors, large-scale Hotel and restaurant employees, have committed crimes in Shaoyang, Loudi, Yueyang, Changsha and other places.

In Linxiang, forest police have found that poaching gangs have hunted and sold as many as 500,000 wild birds in just 40 days. In 2018, local forest police officers found 38 bird-feeding greenhouses scattered across a large secluded clearing. Inside the shed, the dark mass was filled with live caged wild birds, and the ground was littered with the dead bodies of small birds. The wild birds identified at the scene were thrush, Meadow Bunting, small bunting, grey-headed bunting, Yellow-browed Warbler and Stilt Warbler, which are protected by the state.

According to the case investigators, these illegal personnel will illegally capture and purchase wild birds, fatten them up with high-protein, antibiotic and other foods in the shed, then heat them to death in the shed, suffocate them in the bag, and then pack them with ice, by coach to Guangdong and other places for sale.

Tangshan in Hebei Province is situated on the south of Bohai Sea, and has numerous inland rivers and wetlands. The East asia-australia route, one of the world's eight largest migratory routes for migratory birds, passes through here. This is an important stopping place for migratory birds during their migration, more than one million of 70 species of birds migrate through and stay over the winter each year. Among them, there are precious red-crowned crane, Oriental White Stork, Black Stork, Swan and so on, there are also "three" protection birds yellow-breasted bunting (commonly known as Finch) , gray-headed bunting and so on.

This is also where the illegal hunting of wild birds is concentrated. Forest police investigators found that illegal hunters hunted in the fields, bought land, and then concentrated feeding in the fertile areas and Caofeidian District, feeding grains and hormone drugs to fatten them up, while adding large amounts of antibiotics for disease prevention, more than 20 days after the use of plastic bags suffocated, transported to Tianjin, and then airlifted to the south, sold to hotels, restaurants.

Among them, Yellow-breasted Bunting is the most typical, the bird is also known as Hehuaque, Hebei Province's key protected animals, in the south is believed to have the effect of Kidney Impotence, is a hotel restaurant a high-end dishes. "If you catch a small yellow bird (Yellow-breasted Bunting) for 10 yuan, you can sell it for 100 yuan in restaurants across Guangdong, " a local official said

Wuhan is also an important market for "game" 

The outbreak originated in Wuhan, where most of the early confirmed cases came from the south China Seafood Market. The Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention recently made progress in tracing the virus, confirming the presence of a large number of COVID-19 in the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan.

The first financial reporter learned from the Forest Public Security, Wuhan is also a domestic "game" important market.

In 2019, the Heilongjiang Qiqihar cracked the "93 illegal trafficking in wild birds" case and arrested a total of 25 people involved in the case. The case involved a large number of people and a huge number of birds, and involved areas across Heilongjiang and Hubei provinces, daqing, Wuhan and six other cities and counties.

Case officers said that this is a huge hunting, acquisition, trafficking, selling wild animals of the criminal network, and the means of covert crime, communication using code words, anti-detection ability.

Inside the Dorbod Mongol Autonomous County, investigators found that the purchased wildlife was destined for Wuhan. "there was a lot of money flowing in and out with Chu from Wuhan, " he said. "It was initially identified as Chu from Wuhan. At the same time, investigations revealed that most of the people who worked there were villagers from nearby, numbering more than a dozen people. "

In September 2019, investigators went to Wuhan to look for a suspect, surnamed Chu, and confirmed that the place of delivery was Pak Sha Chau agricultural and sideline products market in Wuhan. A total of 81 cartons packed in woven bags and over 3200 wild birds were seized at the scene.

An illegal wildlife trafficking network across the country in Jilin Province. Source: Forest Public Security

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
216 seized, 129 arrested! The largest number of pangolins case in China has been uncovered in Hunan. Source: Forest Public Security

Wuhan's south China Seafood Market, nominally a seafood market, is actually a mixed market. There is wildlife trading in the western district of the south China Seafood Market, especially in the western district's seventh street and the area near the market's interior in Yachimata. There are many wildlife trading shops, where there are various kinds of wildlife, such as bamboo rat, civet cat, wild duck, snake, hare and so on.

Initially found that the diagnosis of dozens of patients, mainly in the south China Seafood Market Wholesale Market Operations, procurement staff. Wuhan Health Commission reported that the first case of the unfortunate death of the infected patient is also perennial in the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan procurement goods.

In December 2015, the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress said that the overall situation of wildlife protection in China is still very grim. The commission's field research in Hainan, Guangxi, Yunnan, Heilongjiang, Jilin and Hubei has found that illegal hunting, killing and trading of wild animals still exist to varying degrees in many places. The abuse of wild animals is still prevalent in some areas.

The State Forestry Administration of the People's Republic of China also said in a 2014 emergency notice on actively responding to the human H7N9 avian influenza epidemic and earnestly doing a good job in monitoring and controlling the epidemic disease in land wild animals in spring, "according to local surveillance reports, since last year, H5N1, H5N2, H9N2 and H10n8 sub-types of avian influenza have occurred in Hebei, Hubei and other places, and five counties (cities) in four regions (states) in Xinjiang have successively broken out small ruminant sheep outbreaks. "

The disadvantage of protection is caused by "reasonable utilization" 

On the 26th of this month, the General Administration of Market Supervision, the Ministry of Agriculture and rural areas, and the State Forestry and Grass Bureau jointly issued the "announcement on banning the trade of wild animals, " requiring that places where wild animals are kept and bred be quarantined, it is strictly forbidden for wild animals to be exported or transported for sale. All agricultural (market) markets, supermarkets, catering units, e-commerce platforms and other places of business, strictly prohibit any form of wildlife trading activities.

"consumers should be fully aware of the health risks of eating wild animals, stay away from 'game' and eat healthily, " the statement said

Previously, on the 24th, the above-mentioned three departments also issued an "urgent notice on strengthening the supervision of the wild animal market and actively carrying out the prevention and control of the epidemic situation, " which called for the raising, breeding, transportation, sale, purchase and other links, strengthen inspection and quarantine, bamboo rats, badgers and other wild animals that may carry COVID-19, the implementation of containment and isolation in their breeding places, strictly prohibit external proliferation, prohibit transshipment trafficking. All other wild animals that have not passed the quarantine inspection shall be strictly prohibited from entering the market. Highlight farmers'markets, supermarkets, restaurants and other key places and websites.

But it remains to be seen how effective these measures will be. The abuse of wild animals in many places, many people's consumption habits have become ingrained.

"Some people have the wrong idea of eating game to nourish the body, and they also have the concept of novelty-seeking consumption and conspicuous consumption, " said the former State Forestry Administration of the People's Republic of China official, who said wildlife products are relatively scarce, the profit margin of illegal operation and sale of wildlife products is relatively large, and there is a certain driving force in the economic interests.

At the same time, hunting, transportation, and communication have become highly technical. The success rate of illegal hunting is higher, the relative damage is greater, and the cost of breaking the law is lower.

China has one of the richest wildlife species in the world, with more than 6,500 species of Vertebrata alone, accounting for about 10 percent of the world's Vertebrata. There are 252 species of wild animals that are more seriously or endangered. Huge wildlife resources, coupled with weak regulatory capacity and certain market demand, make it difficult to stop wildlife consumption and trade.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A wildlife farm in Hebei Province. Photo / Zhang Ke

Another key factor, experts told China Business News, is the long-standing argument that wildlife should be used "rationally" .

Differences of opinion were most acute when the Wildlife Protection Act was amended in 2015. Some experts said that the utilization and consumption of wild animals and their products should abide by laws and regulations and conform to public order and good customs. Zhou Ke, a professor at the Renmin University of China Law School, said that with "Rational Utilization" , the law on wildlife protection actually becomes "the law on Wildlife Exploitation and utilization. ". In his view, "reasonable utilization" and "protection" are incompatible.

However, some officials said that wild animal resources have been accompanied by the origin and development of human society, and people have been constantly using wild animals.

After the outbreak of pneumonia in the COVID-19,19 academicians and scholars from the Chinese Academy of Sciences, Tsinghua University and Peking University issued a joint appeal to stop illegal consumption and trade of wild animals, managing major public health crises at source. Experts say more rigid laws must be put in place to curb the eating and trading of wildlife.

Scientific studies have linked animal outbreaks in recent years to Emerging Infectious Diseases Hendra Setiawan, Nipah, H7N9 bird flu, Ebola and Middle East Respiratory Syndrome, experts said. Statistics show that more than 70% of Emerging Infectious Diseases are derived from animals.

Experts say the viruses are naturally present in the wild and do not necessarily cause disease or death in wild hosts, but their exposure to humans has increased dramatically as humans have eaten wild animals or encroached on wildlife habitats, it creates the conditions for the virus to spread from wild animals to humans, endangering public health. Together with the convenience of transportation and the movement of people, the probability of an epidemic outbreak has increased greatly.
